	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Bregalad's solution would work fine for a 16 KiB ROM (NROM-128), as long as it's properly doubled to fill the ROM. For a 32 KiB ROM (NROM-256), the PRG ROM bank loaded into $8000-$BFFF at power-on is undefined. To use it on an UNROM cart, you'll need to add a stub to the reset handler somewhere in $C000-$FFFF that maps the first bank into $8000-$BFFF:
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">reset_stub:<br />&nbsp; ldx #0<br />&nbsp; stx reset+1<br />&nbsp; jmp real_reset</div>
<br />Then your vectors would be nmi, reset_stub, and irq.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


